The paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model is a generative model, which involves learning complex relationships between two domains, and controlling variations in the mapping. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments on image generation tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
